    "title": "External signer: in case of error shows only \"External signer failure\"",
    "body": "### Is there an existing issue for this?\n\n- [X] I have searched the existing issues\n\n### Current behaviour\n\nShows a dialog with title \"External signer failure\" and description \"External signer failure\".\n\n### Expected behaviour\n\nReport the error that is received as part of the execution result in the `error` field designated for such execution failures/errors.\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\nHave an external signer perform a `signtx` (stdin) operation and report back a result that includes a body to the `error` field of the json.\n\n### Relevant log output\n\nN/A\n\n### How did you obtain Bitcoin Core\n\nPre-built binaries\n\n### What version of Bitcoin Core are you using?\n\nv27.1\n\n### Operating system and version\n\nFedora Linux\n\n### Machine specifications\n\nBasic laptop with Intel CPU. Nothing special.",
